The '''1997 [[Liverpool Victoria]] [[UK Championship (snooker)|UK Championship]]''' took place at the [[Guildhall and Charter Theatre|Guildhall]], [[Preston]] starting on 12 November and TV stages shown on [[BBC]] took place between 22 and 30 November 1997. This was to be the last UK championship to be held in Preston which had held the contest since [[1978 UK Snooker Championship|1978]]. The [[1998 UK Snooker Championship|following year's]] competition would be held in [[Bournemouth]].

[[Ronnie O'Sullivan]] beat [[Stephen Hendry]] 10<U+2013>6 in the final, ending Hendry's run of three successive UK championship wins. O'Sullivan had been the last player other than Hendry to win the event, as a 17-year-old in 1993.

==Prize money==

Winner   <U+00A3>75,000

High break  <U+00A3>5,000

Total   <U+00A3>440,000

==Highest break==

137 [[Stephen Lee]] (TV)

